{"questionId":"33389617","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the minimum distance from the origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> to the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> passes through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">λ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to apply distance formula to find their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced></math> or their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find their minimum value of&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math> using GDC <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>571428</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4285</mn><mo>…</mo></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>OR&nbsp;</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4285</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92792</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>21</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>setting the scalar product of their line and their direction vector to zero<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>14</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>571428</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their value for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi></math> into their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi></math> to find the position vector of the closest point and find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"bold\"><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" stretchy=\"true\">|</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" stretchy=\"true\">|</mo></mstyle></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92792</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>21</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>21</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> be a point on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to find the cross product between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math> and the direction, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></math>, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">j</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">k</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find shortest distance using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mfenced></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>216</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92792</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>21</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33389617","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.11b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the minimum distance from the origin O to the line L.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}